run().details: This function performs the following operations: 1. Creates a fork of Kaia mainnet for testing 2. Starts broadcasting transactions using the private key from environment variables 3. Logs the USDT balance of the OFT adapter contract 4. Withdraws 1 USDT (1e6 wei) from the hardcoded lending pool 5. Stops broadcasting transactions Security considerations: - Uses PRIVATE_KEY from environment variables - ensure this is kept secure - Hardcoded lending pool address should be verified before execution - Withdraws a fixed amount (1e6) - consider making this configurable Usage: forge script CheckBalance --broadcast -vvv

run().notice: Main execution function that checks balances and withdraws liquidity
